Column.value: \brief Function dedicate to override ES1 defaults register map values for PHASE CORRECTION I/Q in all PDC profiles depending on selected output sampling rate(Fsout) This function makes usage of SPI transactions and supports PDC multicast \details This function will override ES1 default register map values for PHASE CORRECTION I/Q using these values. Also the function sets accordingly PDC Equalizer coefficients filter, needed to achieve the full PHASE Correction on I/Q tackling filter group delay. 1. For Steep narrow band mode fsOut / MHz | PDC_PHASE_COR_I | PDC_PHASE_COR_Q ------------ | ------------- |------------- 80 | 1650 | -1213 40 | 1816 | -947 20 | 2043 | 141 10 | 1868 | 840 2. For Narrow band mode fsOut / MHz | PDC_PHASE_COR_I | PDC_PHASE_COR_Q ------------ | ------------- |------------- 80 | 1647 | -1217 40 | 2028 | 283 20 | 1583 | 1299 10 | 1037 | 1766 3. Equalizer coefficients on equalizerCoefficients according to PDC design document Table 17 and TABle 18 combined fsOut / MHz | EQ_COEFF_1 | EQ_COEFF_2 | EQ_COEFF_3 | ------------ | -----------|-----------------|-------------| fsOut / MHz | k0xa1 | k0 or re(k0xa0) | imag(k0xa0) | ------------ | -----------|-----------------|-------------| 80 | 10890 | -5397 (k0) | 0 | 40 | 11335 | -5086 |-3695 | 20 | 11457 | -5283 |-3838 | 10 | 9122 | -1504 |-1093 | \param [in] profileIndex variable indicating the profile to be selected to apply phase correction and EQ coeffs values \param [in] outputSamplingRate sampling rate to be used since this determines the phase correction to use \param [in] filterMode to use since this determines the phase correction to use \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfe_error_none_e is returned
